name: Kiwi Wraps or Rolls
author: FreshBaby.com
summary: Great for back to school lunches! These wraps can be served as a traditional wrap sandwich or slice it into pieces (like a sushi roll) for bite sized treats.
ingredients: ½  kiwi, peeled and thinly sliced
directions: Cut rounded edges from tortilla to form a square
Spread peanut butter on one half of the tortilla; spread cream cheese on remaining half
Place kiwi slices in a single layer over cream cheese
Starting with the cream cheese end, gently roll up the tortilla to form a log shape
Serve as a wrap or sliced into thick rounds
